Tier 3 — seesaw-cloud-agent Enhanced Task List

Title: FastAPI Project Setup and Cloud Run Deploy
Description:
Create the seesaw-cloud-agent repository with the FastAPI application structure: main.py, routers/, agents/, services/, models/, tests/. Add requirements.txt with all production dependencies. Create Dockerfile targeting Python 3.12-slim with uvicorn as the process manager on port 8080. Add cloudbuild.yaml for automated Cloud Run deployment via gcloud builds submit. Deploy a working health check endpoint GET /health that returns {"status": "ok", "version": "1.0.0"}. Verify the Cloud Run URL is reachable from a browser.

Title: Firebase Admin SDK and Firestore Schema Initialisation
Description:
Add firebase-admin to requirements.txt. Create services/firebase.py with a singleton Firestore client initialised from the GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS environment variable. Create services/schema.py that documents and creates the Firestore collections: child_profiles, sessions, parent_configs, published_stories, and safety_logs. Write a scripts/init_schema.py that seeds a test child profile and session document to verify connectivity. Add a tests/test_firestore.py integration test that reads and writes a test document.

Title: POST /story/start Endpoint
Description:
Create routers/story.py and implement the POST /story/start endpoint. It must accept a StoryStartRequest Pydantic model containing session_id, child_profile, scene_context, and on_device_beat. Write the session document to Firestore sessions/{session_id} with status "active", started_at timestamp, and scene context. Write the first beat to the beats subcollection at turn_number: 1. Return {"session_id": ..., "status": "started"} immediately (the enhanced beat comes from the ADK pipeline in T3-009). Write a unit test using httpx.AsyncClient with a mocked Firestore client.

Title: POST /story/beat Endpoint (Passthrough Mode)
Description:
Implement POST /story/beat in routers/story.py. Accept session_id, turn_number, child_answer, on_device_beat, and is_ending_requested. Write the beat record to Firestore sessions/{session_id}/beats/{turn_number} with on_device_text and child_answer fields. Return a 200 response with {"session_id": ..., "turn_number": ..., "status": "saved"}. At this stage, the enhanced_text field is null — Gemini integration is added in T3-009. This makes the endpoint immediately testable from iOS before the ADK pipeline is complete.

Title: POST /sync/beat Endpoint
Description:
Implement POST /sync/beat in routers/story.py. Accept session_id, child_id, and beat_summary (containing characters_introduced, theme, objects_used, child_answer_summary). Update the child's child_profiles/{child_id} document in Firestore, appending new characters to favourite_characters and updating last_session_id. This is the lightweight sync endpoint called fire-and-forget by iOS after every Apple FM turn. Response is always {"status": "synced"} within 200ms. Write a unit test verifying the Firestore update is idempotent.

Title: Context Enricher ADK Agent
Description:
Create agents/context_enricher.py. Implement a Google ADK Agent named context_enricher using gemini-2.0-flash. Define two tools: get_child_memory(child_id: str) (reads child_profiles/{child_id} from Firestore) and get_previous_session(session_id: str) (reads the last 5 beats from the previous session). The agent's instruction must direct it to identify recurring characters, unresolved story threads, and favourite themes from the memory data. Output must be a structured ContextSummary Pydantic model under 300 tokens. Write a unit test mocking the Firestore tools and verifying the output schema.

Title: Enhanced Story Generator ADK Agent
Description:
Create agents/story_generator.py. Implement a Google ADK Agent named enhanced_story_generator using gemini-2.0-flash with response_mime_type: "application/json" and the EnhancedBeat Pydantic output schema. The EnhancedBeat model must include story_text: str, question: str, theme: str, character_memory: list[str], and suggested_next_theme: str. The system instruction must specify 4–6 sentence story segments, age-appropriate vocabulary rules (with age provided in context), and the requirement to incorporate the child's answer naturally. Write a unit test asserting the output story_text references at least one object from the input labels list.

Title: Safety Moderator ADK Agent with Logging
Description:
Create agents/safety_moderator.py. Implement a Google ADK Agent named safety_moderator using gemini-2.0-flash. Define a log_safety_event(session_id, turn_number, failure_reason, original_beat, sanitised_beat) tool that writes to Firestore safety_logs. The agent instruction must check for: violence, fear-inducing content, inappropriate themes, PII leakage, and age-appropriateness violations. Return a SafetyResult model with safety_passed: bool, sanitised_beat: EnhancedBeat | null, and failure_reason: str | null. Write unit tests for five known violation patterns (violence, fear, PII, age-inappropriate vocab, and clean content).

Title: ADK Sequential Pipeline and Full Beat Endpoint
Description:
Create agents/pipeline.py. Assemble SequentialAgent(sub_agents=[context_enricher, story_generator, safety_moderator]) as the seesaw_story_pipeline. Update POST /story/beat to invoke the pipeline asynchronously after writing the passthrough response. When the pipeline completes, update the Firestore beat document with enhanced_text, safety_passed, and tts_audio_url fields. The iOS CloudAgentService polls for this update or receives it via a follow-up request. Write an end-to-end integration test simulating a full 3-turn story session.

Title: Google Cloud TTS Integration
Description:
Create services/tts_service.py. Implement synthesise_beat(text: str, child_age: int, session_id: str, turn_number: int) -> str. Select voice based on age: en-US-Journey-F for ages 3–5, en-US-Neural2-F for ages 6–8. Wrap text in SSML <prosody rate="85%" pitch="+2st"> for a warm, story-appropriate delivery. Upload the resulting MP3 to Cloud Storage at gs://seesaw-audio-beats/{session_id}/beat_{turn_number}.mp3 and return a signed URL with 1-hour expiry. Write a unit test mocking the Cloud TTS client and asserting the signed URL format.

Title: GET /parent/sessions/{child_id} Endpoint
Description:
Implement GET /parent/sessions/{child_id} in routers/parent.py. Query Firestore sessions collection where child_id equals the path parameter, ordered by started_at descending, limited to 20 results. Return a SessionListResponse Pydantic model with sessions: list[SessionSummary] where each SessionSummary includes session_id, started_at, status, total_turns, and theme. Require Firebase Auth JWT validation on this endpoint. Write a unit test with 5 mock sessions asserting correct ordering and pagination.

Title: POST /story/end and Session Closure
Description:
Implement POST /story/end in routers/story.py. Accept session_id, final_beat, and parent_approve_share: bool. Update the Firestore session document: set status to "ended", set ended_at to current timestamp, calculate and store total_turns from the beats subcollection count. If parent_approve_share is true, set status to "publishing_requested" to trigger the Cloud Function in T3-013. Return {"session_id": ..., "status": "ended", "total_turns": N}. Write a unit test verifying the status transition logic.

Title: Cloud Function: Story Publishing Workflow
Description:
Create functions/publish_story.py as a Firebase Cloud Function triggered by Firestore document update when sessions/{session_id}.status == "publishing_requested". The function must: (1) assemble full_text from all beats in the beats subcollection ordered by turn_number; (2) call Gemini to generate a child-friendly title (max 8 words) and summary (max 2 sentences); (3) run a final safety check; (4) write a new document to published_stories; (5) update the session status to "published". Deploy using firebase deploy --only functions. Write an integration test using the Firebase emulator.

Title: POST /publish Direct Endpoint
Description:
Implement POST /publish in routers/parent.py as an alternative to the Cloud Function trigger. This endpoint requires Firebase Auth and share_enabled: true in the parent's parent_config. It runs the same publishing workflow as T3-013 synchronously: assemble story, generate title/summary with Gemini, safety check, write to published_stories. Return {"story_id": ..., "title": ..., "status": "published"}. This endpoint exists for direct parent-initiated sharing from the iOS app's parent dashboard. Write a unit test asserting that a session with share_enabled: false returns 403.

Title: Firebase Auth JWT Validation Middleware
Description:
Create middleware/auth.py. Implement a FastAPI dependency verify_firebase_token(authorization: str = Header(...)) that decodes the Firebase Auth JWT using firebase_admin.auth.verify_id_token(). Extract and return the uid and email claims. Apply this dependency to all /parent/ and /publish routes. The /story/ and /sync/ routes use a lighter API-key check (passed from iOS via X-API-Key header) for child-session calls where full auth would add too much latency. Write unit tests for valid token, expired token, and missing header cases.

Title: Rate Limiting and Error Handling
Description:
Add slowapi to requirements.txt. Apply rate limiting to: POST /story/beat — 100 requests/day per child_id from the request body; POST /story/start — 20 sessions/day per child_id; POST /publish — 5 publishes/day per parent uid. Create a global FastAPI exception handler that returns consistent {"error": {"code": ..., "message": ...}} JSON for all 4xx and 5xx errors. Ensure rate limit exceeded returns 429 with a retry_after header. Write unit tests for each rate limit threshold.

Title: End-to-End Integration Test
Description:
Create tests/test_e2e.py. Simulate a complete 3-turn story session: (1) POST /story/start with a mock child profile and scene context; (2) POST /sync/beat with the first beat summary; (3) two POST /story/beat calls with mock child answers; (4) POST /story/end with parent_approve_share: false. Assert that all Firestore documents are correctly created at each step, the ADK pipeline runs (mocked), safety check passes, and the session status transitions correctly from active to ended. This test must be runnable locally using the Firebase emulator.

